title: Start
---
Lyre: I had a dream last night.
Lyre: There was a woman. Her look was stern, wings adorned her figure.
Lyre: She carries the feeling of dirt between your fingernails.
Lyre: The feeling of the unmoving hills, and the feeling of sacred routines.
Lyre: There is no doubt I know this woman well. Yet of where, I do not know.
Istaya: Lyre.
Istaya: Get up, there is much to do.
